 written expressly for this edition, sets Darwish’s work in the context of changes in the Middle East in the past thirty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  a1982 israeli invasion.  aarabic literature.  abitter rivals.  aconflict.  aengaging.  afate.  agood vs evil.  ahardship.  aheroism.  ahistorical dimensions.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ahomeland.  ahostilities.  ahuman struggles.  aintense.  ainvasion.  alebanon.  alife lessons.  aliterature.  amen at war.  amiddle east history.  apalestine.  apoems.  apoetry collection.  apoetry.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apower struggle.  aprominent poets.  aprose poems.  aresistance.  arevolutionaries.  ashelling of beirut.  aspiritual.  atragic.  aviolence.  awar ravaged streets.  awar.  awarriors.  aworld politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027304740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095459540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954595423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954595/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY